To perform financial calculations, I would use various formulas and techniques. For instance, to calculate the amount due, I would subtract any payments or credits from the original invoice amount. To calculate interest charges, I would use the daily interest rate multiplied by the outstanding principal balance. To calculate balances, I would add or subtract transactions from the previous balance. To calculate discounts, I would apply a percentage discount to the original amount. To calculate equity, I would subtract liabilities from assets. To calculate principal, I would subtract interest from the total payment. These calculations would help me to accurately record and analyze financial transactions.
